(2379, 'document', 'text/html', 'Accommodation', 'general', 'Accommodation', 'accommodation', 'Accommodation', 1, 0, 0, 2372, 0, '', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;line-height:15.75pt;margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;"><strong><span style="font-family:''Poor Richard'', serif;color:#000000;font-size:12pt;">To avoid confusion all accommodation will be pre-allocated prior to your arrival!!</span></strong></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;line-height:15.75pt;margin:0cm 0cm 0pt;"><span style="font-family:''Poor Richard'', serif;color:#000000;font-size:12pt;"></span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height:15.75pt;margin:0cm 0cm 15.75pt;"><strong><span style="font-family:''Poor Richard'', serif;color:#000000;font-size:12pt;">The South Wing</span></strong><span style="font-family:''Poor Richard'', serif;color:#000000;font-size:12pt;"> is a magnificent apartment, sleeping 12.All of thelarger rooms lookout tosplendid views down Loch Aline to Mull. The furniture and fittings are those originally used in the Victorian country house, and are examples of the best work of the period.</span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height:15.75pt;margin:0cm 0cm 15.75pt;"><strong><span style="font-family:''Poor Richard'', serif;color:#000000;font-size:12pt;">The Billiard RoomFlat</span></strong><span style="font-family:''Poor Richard'', serif;color:#000000;font-size:12pt;">sleeps 9 and faces west over some of the finest planting in the garden with views to to the Fuinary Hills beyond. The sitting/dining room of massive proportions was the old billiard room. The kitchen was the old gun room.<br /><br /><strong>The Garden Flat</strong> is on the ground floorwith avast sitting roomlooking over lawns and trees to the Loch and wooded hills beyond.This flat opens directly onto the veranda and lawn.It sleeps5 people.</span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height:15.75pt;margin:0cm 0cm 15.75pt;"><span style="font-family:''Poor Richard'', serif;color:#000000;font-size:12pt;"><strong>The Nursery Flat</strong> is a cosy apartment sleeping6 under the eaves on the second floor of the House.Thesitting room has a large window seat commanding magnificent views over Loch Aline to Mull.<br /><br /><strong>The Top Flat</strong>is on the second floor of the House and sleeps6 witha combined kitchen / dining / sitting room. Cosy rather than grand,2 of the bedrooms have views over the garden</span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height:15.75pt;margin:0cm 0cm 15.75pt;"><strong><span style="font-family:''Poor Richard'', serif;color:#000000;font-size:12pt;">The Boat House</span></strong><span style="font-family:''Poor Richard'', serif;color:#000000;font-size:12pt;"> sleeps 5 with sublime views across Loch Aline. There is a delightful seashore terrace from which otters and sea eagles are frequently seen.</span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height:15.75pt;margin:0cm 0cm 15.75pt;"><strong><span style="font-family:''Poor Richard'', serif;color:#000000;font-size:12pt;">Craigendarrochs</span></strong><span style="font-family:''Poor Richard'', serif;color:#000000;font-size:12pt;"> are a pair of delightful cottages next to each other and alongside the River Aline, sleeping4 &amp;5guests respectively. They are ideal for two families holidaying together.</span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height:15.75pt;margin:0cm 0cm 15.75pt;"><span style="font-family:''Poor Richard'', serif;color:#000000;font-size:12pt;"><strong>Castle Cottage </strong>nestles on the shore of Lochaline under the walls of Kinlochaline Castle. Castle Cottage has a substantial garden over looking the mouth of the River Aline and sleeps6 guests.</span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height:15.75pt;margin:0cm 0cm 15.75pt;"><strong><span style="font-family:''Poor Richard'', serif;color:#000000;font-size:12pt;">Achranich</span></strong><span style="font-family:''Poor Richard'', serif;color:#000000;font-size:12pt;"> is a spacious Victorian property with a large garden that was formerly the factor''s house. Achranich lies close to the working heart of the estate and sleeps up to10 guests in comfort.</span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height:15.75pt;margin:0cm 0cm 15.75pt;"><strong><span style="font-family:''Poor Richard'', serif;color:#000000;font-size:12pt;">Rose Cottage </span></strong><span style="font-family:''Poor Richard'', serif;color:#000000;font-size:12pt;">stands by itself in peace and quiet close to the mouth of the River Aline. Roses grow up the front of this delightful cottage sleeping8 guests.</span></p>\n<p><img src="../../assets/users/paulandmary/images/ardtornish-accommodation-map-3a712f43.jpg" alt="" /></p>', 1, 33, 6, 1, 0, 1, 1346244857, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Accommodation', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'modDocument', 'wedding', 1),
