(2381, 'document', 'text/html', 'Honeymoon wish list', 'general', 'Gift List', 'gift-list', 'Gift List', 1, 0, 0, 2372, 0, '', '<p style="line-height:15.75pt;"><span style="font-family:''Poor Richard'', serif;color:#000000;font-size:13.5pt;">Joining us for our wedding celebrations is gift enough in our eyes however, several of you have asked us about a gift list and we understand that those closest to us may wish to give us something to mark the occasion. Asyou know, travel &amp; food are our 2big passions.<span> </span>Passions which we indulgewhenever possible and we hope, our honeymoon will beno exception! We''re so excited about this celebratory trip to explore2countries whichneither of us has visited.</span></p>\n<p style="line-height:15.75pt;"><span><span><span style="font-family:''Poor Richard'', serif;color:#000000;font-size:13.5pt;">We''ve set up a ''gift list with a twist''. Rather than having traditional items listedyou will findour ''honeymoon wishes''. A list of experiences&amp; activities which combined,will truly make this the trip of a lifetime with memories which will last forever. Gifts varyfromcocktails inDubia, dinner on one of the famous wine estates in Franschook toa trip uptable mountain in Capetown! We''ve certainly had fun coming up with this, we hope you like it too.</span></span></span></p>\n<p style="line-height:15.75pt;"><span><span><span style="font-family:''Poor Richard'', serif;color:#000000;font-size:13.5pt;"><a href="http://www.honeyfund.co.uk/wedding/paulandmary">http://www.honeyfund.co.uk/wedding/paulandmary</a></span></span></span></p>\n<p style="line-height:15.75pt;"><span><span><span style="font-family:''Poor Richard'', serif;color:#000000;font-size:13.5pt;">As you can imagine......Marywas off ordering Lonely Planet guides and researching destinations before we''d even set a date for the wedding or, booked the venue!! <span><span><span></span>As were now all organised we thought you might like a quick nosey at our honeymoon itinerary:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\n<p style="line-height:15.75pt;"><strong><span style="font-family:''Times New Roman'';font-size:medium;">Dubai:</span></strong><span style="font-family:Georgia, serif;color:#000000;font-size:10.5pt;"> </span><span style="font-family:''Poor Richard'', serif;color:#000000;font-size:13.5pt;">The first stopof our trip will be Dubia! We have2 daysat The Bonnington Hotel torelax and recharge the batteries followingthe wedding.Dubai isa place weve travelled through on many occasions but somewhere weve never actually stopped. On this occasion,we look forward to exploring! From there, well fly to Johannesburg and transfer directly toPetoria.</span></p>\n<p style="line-height:15.75pt;"><strong><span style="font-family:''Poor Richard'', serif;color:#000000;font-size:13.5pt;">Pretoria &amp; The Rovos Rail:</span></strong><span style="font-family:''Poor Richard'', serif;color:#000000;font-size:13.5pt;"> <span></span>Well stay here overnight at the Villa Amor before catching the luxurious Rovos Rail train for a 1000 mile journey through the heart of the country,arriving in Cape Town2 days later.</span></p>\n<p style="line-height:15.75pt;"><strong><span style="font-family:''Poor Richard'', serif;color:#000000;font-size:13.5pt;">Capetown:</span></strong><span style="font-family:''Poor Richard'', serif;color:#000000;font-size:13.5pt;"><span> </span>Duringour5 days in Cape Town we plan to explore the city sampling everything thatit has to offerincludinga day diving with Great White sharks! Cape Town is the gateway to the wonderful wine lands of South Africa where we plan to make Franschook our base for the next 3 days.</span></p>\n<p style="line-height:15.75pt;"><strong><span style="font-family:''Poor Richard'', serif;color:#000000;font-size:13.5pt;">Franschhoek:</span></strong><span style="font-family:''Poor Richard'', serif;color:#000000;font-size:13.5pt;"> We will be staying for 3 nights at La Petite Ferme which is situated o</span><span style="font-family:Georgia, serif;font-size:10.5pt;">n the side of a mountain, overlooking the Franschhoek valley.<span> </span>Our suite is set amongst the vineyards!! </span></p>\n<p style="line-height:15.75pt;"><span style="font-family:''Poor Richard'', serif;color:#000000;font-size:13.5pt;"><span></span>Some of the best restaurants in the world are situated in this area so we hope to enjoy a few wonderful dinners together as husband and wife.</span></p>\n<p style="line-height:15.75pt;"><span><span><strong><span style="font-family:''Poor Richard'', serif;color:#000000;font-size:13.5pt;">Plettenbery Bay:</span></strong><span style="font-family:''Poor Richard'', serif;color:#000000;font-size:13.5pt;"><span> </span>Leaving thewinelands behind us we willdrive along the famous Garden Route stopping off for 2 nights at Hogshollow, Plettenberg. From here well continue on to the highlight of our trip.</span></span></span></p>\n<p style="line-height:15.75pt;"><strong><span style="font-family:''Poor Richard'', serif;color:#000000;font-size:13.5pt;">Safari:</span></strong><span style="font-family:''Poor Richard'', serif;color:#000000;font-size:13.5pt;"><span> </span>Saving the best till last!<span> </span>We end our time in South Africa with 3 nights at the Amakhala Bush Lodge Game Reserve with the chance to see Africa''s big 5.</span><span style="font-size:medium;"><span style="font-family:''Times New Roman'';"><span> </span>As with all good things, this journey will then come to an end as we fly from Port Elizabeth to Johannasburg to catch our long flight home......</span></span></p>\n<p style="line-height:15.75pt;"><span><span><span style="font-family:''Poor Richard'', serif;color:#000000;font-size:13.5pt;">Once home we will bore you all with our tales and many, many photographs!</span></span></span></p>', 1, 33, 8, 1, 0, 1, 1346244857, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Gift List', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'modDocument', 'wedding', 1);
